sql:
SELECT AVG(performance_score) AS avg_performance_score
FROM cdns
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) as active_video_types_count
FROM video_types
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM video_platforms 
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT performance_score
FROM cdns
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT title, duration, upload_date
FROM videos
WHERE plt_id IN (SELECT plt_id FROM video_platforms WHERE is_active = 1);

external_knowledge:
- Above-average upload dates refers to videos in the top half of the cumulative distribution of upload dates;
- High streaming bandwidth means the average bandwidth is greater than 1000 kbps;
- Good quality ratings imply an average rating greater than 3 out of 5.
